      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEM N EM NZ (9) is in good form having placed from wide barriers in both outings since a Wagga win. Should enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw, with the sprint lane in play. Won the only time she raced here so could prove tough to beat. SUNSET JAY JAY (10) led and kept going to score by 5m here last week. That victory meant she has won the last two times she has raced here with a second at Menangle in between. Draws on the back row this time but she is going well. BETTING STAR (3) produced a good effort last time out when she came from this barrier and finished runner-up at Penrith. Contender. DUFFY HOLLOW NZ (8) draws wide but is racing well with a win and two seconds from the last three starts here.",
